t3204.text: So there’s my sea-hunt day in a nutshell. I have plenty to share with my MH guy on Thursday .... How was your day? And are you going back to the office any time soon? I was hoping to get another review out tonight. That won’t be happening

t3205.text: Seems she was rushed out of there as well and couldn’t debrief as she usually does. Was almost locked in at the hospital! Which wouldn’t be a prob except this is the same hospital that kept her 24hr in an ED recliner bc they had “no beds” in November

t3206.text: I get back and have still to finish my workday. Hard stuff can bite a dick. The easy stuff, on which I have been waiting since January, takes a half hour more than usual. I finish up just as MrsG gets home from her treatment

t3207.text: An Hour Later we’re called in for his flujab. People are queued for various treatments which are being provided by ONE NURSE. Once we are called he is in and out in mere seconds. Meanwhile some cove who has been there 10min starts arcing up at the delay

t3208.text: Mast9’s flujab is done in he treatment room. I am rushing bc doctor wants to leave. She does my referral and checks sth else out. She questions the flujab we’d bought at Terry White Stanhope but sees that it’s OK. We head over to the treatment room

t3209.text: We get there and there’s a pre-access COVID-queue making sure we’re not sick. Then we get to the desk and are told Doctor finishes at 1:15 and may not be able to see us. Why would a doctor accept bookings up until 15min prior to her bunking off? We were eventually seen at 13:30

t3211.text: The day progresses and it seems I can’t get a roll on. When I finally achieve something it’s time to get Mast9 to his flujab appointment. MrsG tells me it’s 1; I was aiming for 1:15. Apparently I had transposed the times in my head

t3212.text: Stress Levels. Let me tell you about stress levels Log in at 6 to start my day. Boss wants to do my mid-cycle review face-to-face. When are you coming in? I wasn’t planning to until this all blows over. We decided tomorrow week
